rowed for two weeks   Current periodicals do not circulate  but we have a photocopy machine available  and copies are free for faculty  Faculty may also make free copies from micro film and  fiche printers  Renewals  Books and bound serials must be physically returned to the library each April but may be borrowed again for another academic year   A V and Recreational Reading materials may be renewed by phone  464 7129  in person  no need to bring the items with you  at My Library  see below  or by replying to an e mail overdue notice  My Library  My Library allows you to view your library record  renew items  place holds  and update your contact information   To log in  enter your VMI network username and password  Other Useful Information   If another patron requests the use of an item you have checked out  that item will be recalled  We appreciate your cooperation in returning recalled materials   Circulation staff will be happy to search for any item that is not found in its correct location   VMI faculty enjoy faculty borrowing privileges at the W L libraries  Simply take your VMI ID card when you visit to set up an account  If you have questions or comments  please feel free to contact Lt  Col  Susan Hastings  at 464 7607 or hastingssf vmi edu      VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 